        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 1:17AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 116 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gail, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gail.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
